  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to clarity when sending group chat messages so that I won't be confused about who has seen it.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen a user sends a message in a public chat there is an erroneous label that reports the message was seen by everyone. This message is shown even when the device is in airplane mode!\r\n\r\nCurrently Status does not report on read/seen status, so this message is wrong and confusing.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\n\r\nSend a message. The label reports `sent`.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\n\r\nSend a message. The label reports `seen by everyone` even when offline.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Join a public chat\r\n- Send a message\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\nRemove the `seen by everyone` label.\r\n\r\nSending messages in group chats should follow the conventions in https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/3784",
